# Multi-Repo Workspace

<!-- Use this when your project has multiple repositories in one workspace. -->
<!-- Place at the parent directory that contains all repos. -->

## Repository Layout

```
workspace/
├── frontend/     # Frontend repository (separate git repo)
├── backend/      # Backend repository (separate git repo)
└── AGENTS.md     # This file (parent directory, NOT a git repo)
```

## Frontend Context

- **Stack:** [e.g., Next.js 15 + TypeScript + Tailwind]
- **Entry:** `frontend/src/app/`
- **API Client:** `frontend/src/lib/api/client.ts`
- **Auth:** [e.g., Google OAuth → JWT → httpOnly cookies via proxy]
- **Key Docs:** `frontend/CLAUDE.md`, `frontend/README.md`

## Backend Context

- **Stack:** [e.g., Django 6 + DRF + PostgreSQL + Redis + Celery]
- **Entry:** `backend/manage.py`, startup script
- **Apps:** [e.g., accounts, projects, timesheets]
- **Settings:** `backend/settings/` (base, development, production)
- **Key Docs:** `backend/CLAUDE.md`, `backend/README.md`

## Auth Flow

```
Browser → Frontend proxy (/api/proxy/*) → Backend API → Database
           │ Adds auth headers              │ Validates JWT
           │ Refreshes expired tokens       │ Checks permissions
           └────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Role Model

<!-- Document your role/permission model -->
| Role | Frontend Access | Backend Group |
|------|----------------|---------------|
| Admin | Full admin panel | `Admins` |
| Manager | Team dashboards | `Managers` |
| Employee | Own data only | `Employees` |

## Development Notes

- Parent directory is NOT a git repo — commit in each repo separately
- Frontend runs on port 3000, Backend on port 8000
- Always run type-check (`npx tsc --noEmit`) before committing frontend
- Always run format (`ruff format .`) before committing backend

